FROM BINARIES
Download the binaries for your operating system from 
https://github.com/MilanSkocic/codata/releases.
The archives contains 3 folders bin, lib and share that you can simply
copy/paste somewhere on your PATH (usually $HOME/.local).
For Windows, you can a .local folder to your %USERPROFILE% and add it
to your PATH.

$ unzip codata-linux-x86_64-2.5.2.zip codata
$ cp -v codata/* your/path/



FROM SOURCES
You need to install fpm (Fortran Package Manager) which can be downloaded
at https://github.com/fortran-lang/fpm/releases/. 
A Makefile allows to compile the static and the shared library. It uses
fpm for compiling the dependencies and the source code.

$ ./configure.sh
$ make
$ make install



PYTHON WRAPPER
If you also need to build the Python wrapper. There is script build.sh
which builds the static and shared library and also the Python wrapper.

$ ./configure.sh
$ ./build.sh
